main event: On May 25, 1959, in Pensacola, FL, an oval-shaped object the size of a pan was observed floating for approximately 5 minutes with 5 HQ photographs taken.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 5 minutes, allowing for extensive observation.
5 high-quality photographs were taken during the sighting.
The investigation officer considered the possibility of the object being an anti-collision light.
The report contains detailed coordinates and azimuth information of the sighting.
A ground-visual observation using binoculars was conducted by a trained operator.
